{"id":55252,"date":"2018-03-12T05:02:20","date_gmt":"2018-03-12T09:02:20","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/staging.budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/?p=55252"},"modified":"2020-12-14T13:25:40","modified_gmt":"2020-12-14T18:25:40","slug":"how-journal-completely-changed-my-finances","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/how-journal-completely-changed-my-finances\/","title":{"rendered":"How a Journal Completely Changed My Finances"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><em>[Oh do I have a good story for you guys today!! I hope you like long-form posts, because my man <strong>Ryland<\/strong> from TheHiddenGreen.com stops by the blog today to pour his heart out to us&#8230; Amazing how much your life can change when you find something that *clicks*! And shockingly, it wasn&#8217;t a budget that did it for him ;) Take it away, Ryland!]<\/em><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">********<\/p>\n<p><strong>I was 23 and crying.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>I had just graduated college after working my tail off.<\/p>\n<p>I had received $100k in scholarships to pay for school, founded a nonprofit while there and won numerous awards for my work.<\/p>\n<p>I thought I had done everything right.<\/p>\n<p><strong>But I missed one piece of the puzzle &#8211; my finances.<\/strong> And there I was, in my black 2007 Nissan Xterra, with tears in my eyes because of it.<\/p>\n<p>This is where my financial life started, and I owe it all to a little journaling.<\/p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s the story of how I went from broke to over $100,000 in my accounts and completely changing my life in the process.<\/p>\n<h2>Zilch Financial Knowledge and $7k of Debt<\/h2>\n<p>In 2007 I had just walked out of an accounting office.<\/p>\n<p>I had been told I owed almost $7,000 in taxes &#8211; of which $7,000 I did not have, nor with any income to pay it back.<\/p>\n<p>That $7k may sound small to some, but I can tell you it\u2019s enough to make you drop your head in your hands and wonder how the hell you got there.<\/p>\n<p><strong>It&#8217;s enough to feel scared.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>I\u2019ve always been someone who worked hard and tried to do the right things, but I\u2019ve also always been someone (maybe behind the scenes) who struggled with money.<\/p>\n<p>Let me give you one example.<\/p>\n<p>In college I was up to get an award for my work and needed a suit. So I went to Nordstrom and tried on the $200, the $500 and the $800 suits.<\/p>\n<p>Which did I get?<\/p>\n<p>The $1,271 suit.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55256\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/1200-dollar-suit.jpg\" alt=\"$1,200 suit\" width=\"458\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/1200-dollar-suit.jpg 458w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/1200-dollar-suit-229x300.jpg 229w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 458px) 100vw, 458px\" \/><\/center><strong>I\u2019ve never wanted a luxurious life, but somehow I\u2019d do stuff like that all the time.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>And at that moment it was hitting me&#8230;<\/p>\n<p>I sat there with tears rolling down my cheeks trying to figure out how I could pay it off.<\/p>\n<p>When I got home I pulled up a Google Sheet (this exact one <a href=\"https:\/\/docs.google.com\/spreadsheets\/d\/1sBCoAInIDKkEtfrXzkaKSkUXBDWvlvfV5fO3W-BFOEE\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">here<\/a>) and gave my first petty attempt at building a budget.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55257\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/youre-fcked-budget.jpg\" alt=\"youre f*cked budget\" width=\"500\" height=\"404\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/youre-fcked-budget.jpg 500w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/youre-fcked-budget-300x242.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/center><strong>To say the least, I hate budgets.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>(Sorry, J. Money. I guess I\u2019m just into other things\u2026)<\/p>\n<p>After a few hours of thinking it through, I decided to sell my car, most of my surfboards, as well as my professional trumpet to pay it off.<\/p>\n<p>That sucked.<\/p>\n<p>But it forced me into an uncomfortable place and brought about self-motivation to create a better life for myself.<\/p>\n<h2>Stop Budgeting, Start Journaling<\/h2>\n<p>About a month later I got my first job.<\/p>\n<p>It was one of those jobs at a company that makes your mom proud.<\/p>\n<p>Here look. She even took this picture of me on &#8220;Ryland\u2019s first day of work.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55259\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/first-day-of-work.jpg\" alt=\"first day of work\" width=\"320\" height=\"239\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/first-day-of-work.jpg 320w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/first-day-of-work-300x224.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px\" \/><\/center>Cute, right?<\/p>\n<p>To be honest, I was excited about it too, but I knew from day one that it wasn\u2019t going to be my end-all-be-all.<\/p>\n<p>I wanted to have more time to work on the things I was passionate about. I wanted to take a few trips a year without breaking the bank. And I wanted to make enough money to live a fun, yet simple life.<\/p>\n<p>I remember thinking, &#8220;Is that really too much to ask for?&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>No way.<\/p>\n<p><strong>But the biggest thing holding me back at that time was my money situation.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>I didn\u2019t know how to make it work for me.<\/p>\n<p>I tried budgeting and that (obviously) didn\u2019t work. I tried putting cash in categorized envelopes, but that didn\u2019t work either.<\/p>\n<p>Everything I tried just wasn\u2019t for me.<\/p>\n<p>But what <em>was <\/em>for me was writing lists.<\/p>\n<p>I wrote one almost every day. I still do. Here&#8217;s my list right now.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55260\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/ryland-list.jpg\" alt=\"ryland list\" width=\"375\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/ryland-list.jpg 375w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/ryland-list-225x300.jpg 225w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 375px) 100vw, 375px\" \/><\/center><strong>From doing that for years I had grown this belief that *what you write* becomes your life.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>So back then, while stuck in my hard place, I decided to write a list.<\/p>\n<p>I wrote out a few lines in my journal of what I wanted to accomplish just for that month.<\/p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s exactly what it looked like:<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55261\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/july-goals-list.jpg\" alt=\"july goals list\" width=\"375\" height=\"459\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/july-goals-list.jpg 375w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/july-goals-list-245x300.jpg 245w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 375px) 100vw, 375px\" \/><\/center>Pretty basic, right?<\/p>\n<p>A few weeks after, something interesting started to happen.<\/p>\n<p><strong>I noticed myself going back to look at the list every few days. In it I\u2019d see the things that deep down I wanted to accomplish, and almost subconsciously my mind would refocus on how to bring them to fruition.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>It was so helpful that at the end of that month I wanted to do it again.<\/p>\n<p>But when my fingertips began writing the next list, my mind kept looking back at the old one.<\/p>\n<p>I had unfinished business.<\/p>\n<p>The old list was calling for an honest reflection, and so that\u2019s what I did.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55262\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/july-goals-list-reflection.jpg\" alt=\"july goals - reflection\" width=\"600\" height=\"723\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/july-goals-list-reflection.jpg 600w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/july-goals-list-reflection-249x300.jpg 249w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/center>Yep, I failed on some items.<\/p>\n<p>But that didn\u2019t matter. The only thing that mattered was continuing to write &#8211; continuing to bring the life I wanted into reality.<\/p>\n<p>So I wrote next month\u2019s list and at the end of that month, I wrote about how I did.<\/p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s a look at that one too:<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55263\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/august-goals-list-reflection.jpg\" alt=\"august goals list reflection\" width=\"608\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/august-goals-list-reflection.jpg 608w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/august-goals-list-reflection-228x300.jpg 228w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" \/><\/center>There wasn\u2019t some special format, outline or directions to follow, and it felt great because of it.<\/p>\n<p>This is my life. It doesn\u2019t fit perfectly inside anyone else\u2019s lines.<\/p>\n<p>My goal became one thing: Write.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Every. Damn. Month.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>And that\u2019s what I did.<\/p>\n<p>I wrote down things like &#8220;eating only nuts, fruits, veggies and fish,&#8221; and other things like &#8220;doing push ups, pulls ups and stretching&#8221; each morning.<\/p>\n<p>Along with those things I wrote down how to make money work.<\/p>\n<p>I wrote out where I wanted my savings account balance to be at the end of each month.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55264\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/monetary-goals-list.jpg\" alt=\"monetary goals list\" width=\"375\" height=\"430\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/monetary-goals-list.jpg 375w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/monetary-goals-list-262x300.jpg 262w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 375px) 100vw, 375px\" \/><\/center>I mapped out how my credit card worked with my paycheck and bank accounts.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55266\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/appreciating-cash-flow-diagram.jpg\" alt=\"appreciating cash flow diagram\" width=\"500\" height=\"344\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/appreciating-cash-flow-diagram.jpg 500w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/appreciating-cash-flow-diagram-300x206.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/center>And I made a list of all the quality items I wanted to have in my life, so I could focus on buying things that really made me happy rather than $1,271 suits.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55267\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/quality-gear-lists.jpg\" alt=\"quality gear lists\" width=\"600\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/quality-gear-lists.jpg 600w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/quality-gear-lists-225x300.jpg 225w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/center>Did I hit every goal every month? Hell no.<\/p>\n<p>Did I write like clockwork on first of every month? Hell no.<\/p>\n<p>But I did it.<\/p>\n<p>Slowly and surely things started to change. Here\u2019s what happened.<\/p>\n<h2>Getting a Grip on My Money<\/h2>\n<p>While writing my goals, I began wanting to learn how other people accomplished the things I wanted.<\/p>\n<p>I Googled everything I was interested in, and came across a whole underground movement of people that were designing their life for the things I was after.<\/p>\n<p>It was magical.<\/p>\n<p>I came across the legends: <a href=\"http:\/\/www.mrmoneymustache.com\/2012\/01\/13\/the-shockingly-simple-math-behind-early-retirement\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Mr. Money Mustache<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/retiring-early-means-being-financially-free\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">J. Money<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.madfientist.com\/the-perfect-life\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">The Mad Fientist<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>(I linked to my favorite article by each of them above, if you&#8217;re interested)<\/p>\n<p><strong>And I read everything. Seriously, everything.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>One of the most important things I learned was the importance of hitting this number called your &#8220;savings rate&#8221; every month and year.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55268\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/savings-rate-number.jpg\" alt=\"savings rate number\" width=\"436\" height=\"254\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/savings-rate-number.jpg 436w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/savings-rate-number-300x175.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 436px) 100vw, 436px\" \/><\/center>By tracking that <em><strong>one number<\/strong><\/em> you can get a ballpark estimate of how long it\u2019ll take for your investments (your passive income) to cover your lifestyle cost (your normal spending).<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-55269\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/savings-ratio-years-to-freedom.jpg\" alt=\"savings ratio - years to freedom\" width=\"271\" height=\"557\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/savings-ratio-years-to-freedom.jpg 310w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/savings-ratio-years-to-freedom-146x300.jpg 146w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 271px) 100vw, 271px\" \/><\/center>To me, that was perfect.<\/p>\n<p><strong>All I needed to do was hit that number and I\u2019d know I was on track.<\/strong> I went off and built a whole automated system that became my personal financial dashboard.<\/p>\n<p>From it I could see my net worth.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-55270\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/ryland-net-worth.jpg\" alt=\"ryland net worth\" width=\"525\" height=\"254\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/ryland-net-worth.jpg 608w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/ryland-net-worth-300x145.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 525px) 100vw, 525px\" \/><\/center>I could see my net income.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55271\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/ryland-net-income-graph.jpg\" alt=\"ryland net income graph\" width=\"594\" height=\"276\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/ryland-net-income-graph.jpg 594w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/ryland-net-income-graph-300x139.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 594px) 100vw, 594px\" \/><\/center>And I could track my savings rate too.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55272\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/ryland-savings-rate-graph.jpg\" alt=\"ryland savings rate graph\" width=\"416\" height=\"453\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/ryland-savings-rate-graph.jpg 416w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/ryland-savings-rate-graph-275x300.jpg 275w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 416px) 100vw, 416px\" \/><\/center><strong>My net worth started going up month after month, and it felt awesome.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>For the first six months, I just shoveled money into my savings account trying to hit the balance I wrote in my journal each month.<\/p>\n<p>That worked great, but I began wondering when I should start investing, 401k-ing, Roth IRA-ing\u2026<\/p>\n<p>You know, all that adult-ing stuff.<\/p>\n<p>That\u2019s when I came across the godfather of this underground movement, <a href=\"http:\/\/jlcollinsnh.com\/2011\/06\/08\/how-i-failed-my-daughter-and-a-simple-path-to-wealth\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Jim Collins<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55273\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/jim-collins-godfather.jpg\" alt=\"jim collins godfather\" width=\"500\" height=\"255\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/jim-collins-godfather.jpg 500w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/jim-collins-godfather-300x153.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/center>I read his entire <a href=\"http:\/\/jlcollinsnh.com\/stock-series\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">stock series<\/a> and so much of his blog that I told my girlfriend I felt like he was my long lost Uncle while on a date one night.<\/p>\n<p>(Even with a comment like that I still couldn\u2019t get her to read his stuff!)<\/p>\n<p>From him I learned 90% of everything I\u2019d ever need to know about investing, and I figured out what to do with my money. [Editor&#8217;s Note: Jim was the catapult of <a href=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/lazy-one-fund-investing-strategy\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">my (J. Money&#8217;s) investing strategies<\/a> as well. Great teacher!]<\/p>\n<p>To jump four years ahead for one moment, here\u2019s a look back at where I put my monthly net income (savings) each month.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55274\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/order-of-investments.jpg\" alt=\"order of investments\" width=\"500\" height=\"238\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/order-of-investments.jpg 500w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/order-of-investments-300x143.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/center>I\u2019d work on one step until I maxed it out, and then I\u2019d move on to the next.<\/p>\n<p>The only thing I might recommend you change from the list above is the investing related lines.<\/p>\n<p>Why?<\/p>\n<p>Because I\u2019ve learned that once there you have three paths to choose from: <a href=\"http:\/\/jlcollinsnh.com\/stock-series\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Paper Assets (aka The Stock Market)<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.coachcarson.com\/start\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Real Estate<\/a> or <a href=\"https:\/\/www.growthlab.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Business<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>By doing a little research you can choose the investment class (or combination of classes) that\u2019s best for <em>you. <\/em>(I\u2019ve linked to the three best resources I know in those links above to point you in the right direction)<\/p>\n<p><strong>So this is how my puzzle pieces began coming together.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>But I want to make one thing clear.<\/p>\n<p>My whole journey above didn\u2019t go down smoothly. It was messy, hard and even disappointing at times.<\/p>\n<p>It was life.<\/p>\n<p>I just kept writing. I just kept going.<\/p>\n<p>Here are a few real-life highlights from how it went down.<\/p>\n<h2>What You Write Becomes Your Life (And $10,000 Mistakes)<\/h2>\n<p>I really don\u2019t believe my life was that different than my peers.<\/p>\n<p>But there were differences.<\/p>\n<p>I\u2019d say the most helpful differences were how I handled these three parts of my life: Housing, Cars and Travel.<\/p>\n<p>Let me tell you what I mean.<\/p>\n<h3><strong>Housing<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p>&#8220;I will never move back in with my parents.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>I said those 9 words hundreds of times to my friends in college. In my mind there was no way, no how that I\u2019d move home after graduation.<\/p>\n<p>Welp\u2026<\/p>\n<p>That was the first thing I did.<\/p>\n<p>One unforeseen benefit of the job I had landed was that the office was about 15 miles from my parents\u2019 house.<\/p>\n<p>I remember driving home from college with my dad and all my stuff in the back of his truck. We pulled into the driveway and my neighbor came out to say, &#8220;hello.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55275\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/neighbors-waving-hello.jpg\" alt=\"neighbors waving hello\" width=\"500\" height=\"409\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/neighbors-waving-hello.jpg 500w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/neighbors-waving-hello-300x245.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/center>I was so embarrassed.<\/p>\n<p>I couldn\u2019t believe I was moving back home.<\/p>\n<p>We met with a brotherly handshake, and one of the first things I said was &#8220;Yeah, man, I\u2019m only going to be here for a month. I\u2019m already looking for spots in the city.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Wrong again&#8230;<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>I ended up staying for 11 whole months.<\/p>\n<p>But this action made a huge difference for me, especially at the start.<\/p>\n<p>I was paying $400\/mo in rent while my peers were paying $1,400\/mo for rent in San Francisco. That put an extra $1,000 in my wallet every month ($12,000 over a year).<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55276\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/living-at-home-savings.jpg\" alt=\"living at home savings\" width=\"500\" height=\"330\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/living-at-home-savings.jpg 500w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/living-at-home-savings-300x198.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/center>Beyond that, I loved that my rent went to people I knew and loved, and, by being more of an adult, I built a new relationship with my parents which was great.<\/p>\n<p>I know this option isn\u2019t available for everyone.<\/p>\n<p>But if I could talk to my old self without the \u201cmove in with parents\u201d option, I\u2019d tell myself to reach out to family friends, extended family or whoever I could to see what is possible.<\/p>\n<p>In the end though, my parents are my parents and I needed freedom.<\/p>\n<p>I wanted to live in an awesome apartment in the city. For me, that was one near the beach, close enough to bike to work and shared with great people.<\/p>\n<p><strong>I started asking friends and coworkers if they\u2019d want to move into a place like that if I found one.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Key point &#8211; \u201cIf I found one.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>I didn\u2019t want anyone on a 14-day or 30-day time schedule to make the jump. I wanted to move only if the perfect apartment came up.<\/p>\n<p>I ended up finding two great coworkers who loved the idea and hopped on board.<\/p>\n<p>Together we hacked Craigslist to send us any new listings that matched our \u201cperfect apartment\u201d specifications.<\/p>\n<p>And in one month here\u2019s what we found:<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-55277\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/sunset-windows-apartment.jpg\" alt=\"sunset windows apartment\" width=\"581\" height=\"406\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/sunset-windows-apartment.jpg 640w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/sunset-windows-apartment-300x210.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 581px) 100vw, 581px\" \/><\/center>Epic.<\/p>\n<p>I took the small office room that was connected to the living room by a sliding door for $1,000\/mo.<\/p>\n<p>It was a great price, but I\u2019d be lying if I said that room was perfect.<\/p>\n<p>There were definitely nights where people wanted to stay up many hours later than I preferred. But for the most part, I was respectful about hanging out with everyone late and my housemates were respectful about the noise.<\/p>\n<p>(Pro tip for noisy rooms: Earplugs. They saved me numerous times.)<\/p>\n<p>All in all this rent kept me well below the city\u2019s average rent, giving me an extra $400\/mo ($4,800\/yr) to stash beyond my peers.<\/p>\n<p>Living in that apartment with good housemates at that price was another huge help.<\/p>\n<p>But not everything went that smoothly\u2026<\/p>\n<h3><strong>The Car. The F\u2014in\u2019 Car<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p>Maybe I\u2019m weird, but I\u2019ve always had this love-hate relationship with cars.<\/p>\n<p>I love the flexibility they provide for my life, but I hate how much they cost when things go wrong.<\/p>\n<p>Let me tell you why.<\/p>\n<p>Three months after starting my job I started searching for a car. I searched and searched and searched, and felt like I\u2019d never find the right one.<\/p>\n<p>One day I came across some ol\u2019 Swedish wheels \u2014 a 2001 Volvo XC70 (a wagon) for $5,400.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55278\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/2001-volvo-XC70-wagon.jpg\" alt=\"2001 volvo XC70 wagon\" width=\"500\" height=\"348\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/2001-volvo-XC70-wagon.jpg 500w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/2001-volvo-XC70-wagon-300x209.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/center>My dad drove me about 45 minutes to test drive it.<\/p>\n<p>I was so tired of searching for cars that I decided then and there that I\u2019m just going to buy this thing.<\/p>\n<p>Wrong decision.<\/p>\n<p>After eight months, a Baja California surf trip (that ended with a tuna can lid duct taped over a missing piece of the engine) and $6,500 in unforeseen maintenance costs later, I sold that piece of junk for $1,900.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55279\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/volvo-breakdown-pic.jpg\" alt=\"volvo breakdown pic\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/volvo-breakdown-pic.jpg 500w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/volvo-breakdown-pic-300x225.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/center>That\u2019s a $10,000 loss. In 8 months.<\/p>\n<p>I still facepalm when I think about that.<\/p>\n<p>From that day forward I went into car-diac arrest for nearly a year.<\/p>\n<p>I sold it a few days after I moved biking distance from work (5 miles), and began using my bike as my daily mobility for 3 months.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55280\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/biking-pals.jpg\" alt=\"biking pals\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/biking-pals.jpg 500w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/biking-pals-300x225.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/center>It was great. I listened to so many amazing podcasts, came in to work energized and my body never felt better.<\/p>\n<p>After a few months of that I bought a 125cc Yamaha Vino Scooter for $1,800.<\/p>\n<p>Getting the scooter was the perfect transition into getting a car (and the ladies totally love the goofy looking scooter vibes).<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55281\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/125cc-yamaha-vino-scooter.jpg\" alt=\"125cc yamaha vino scooter\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/125cc-yamaha-vino-scooter.jpg 500w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/125cc-yamaha-vino-scooter-300x225.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/center>After about 8 months of my bike, scooter, car share program, it became time to get a car again.<\/p>\n<p>This time I thought through what I needed the car to do.<\/p>\n<p>I wanted something that I could pack up with gear, throw surfboards on top and drive to Big Sur for weekend adventures with a friend or two.<\/p>\n<p><strong>I then used these guidelines to help meet my money goals:<\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Buy a car that\u2019s at least five years old (<a href=\"https:\/\/www.driversselect.com\/depreciation.htm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">here\u2019s why<\/a>)<\/li>\n<li>Find a car I like from this list of the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.mrmoneymustache.com\/2012\/03\/19\/top-10-cars-for-smart-people\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">top 10 cars for smart people<\/a><\/li>\n<li>Get a peer-recommended mechanic to look at the car before buying<\/li>\n<li>Toyota or Honda. Period.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>What\u2019d I get?<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55282\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/2005-scion-XA.jpg\" alt=\"2005 Scion XA\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/2005-scion-XA.jpg 500w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/2005-scion-XA-125x125.jpg 125w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/2005-scion-XA-300x300.jpg 300w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/2005-scion-XA-144x144.jpg 144w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/center>A 2005 Scion XA for $4,000 flat with insurance, registration and taxes.<\/p>\n<p>(Scion is a less expensive brand of Toyota)<\/p>\n<p>Compared to the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cars.com\/articles\/heres-what-the-average-new-car-costs-1420694975814\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">average new car price<\/a>, that purchase saved me about $26,000.<\/p>\n<p>It\u2019s taken my girlfriend and I on a 2,000 mile road trip through the Western US, has taken me on multiple surf adventures and, after 3 years, is still running strong!<\/p>\n<h3><strong>Travel<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p>For my first year back I didn\u2019t do much &#8220;plane&#8221; traveling.<\/p>\n<p>Instead, I did tons of weekend trips. My usual schedule looked like this:<\/p>\n<p>I\u2019d pack my surfboard, bike and running shoes in my car and take off at sunrise to Santa Cruz.<\/p>\n<p>I\u2019d surf in the morning, eat a little food and then do a run nearby. In the afternoon I\u2019d meet up with family friends for lunch or tea or just write in my journal overlooking the sea.<\/p>\n<p>Then on the way home I\u2019d go for a small hike, walk or bike ride, sometimes with friends.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55283\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/lake-fun-with-friends.jpg\" alt=\"lake fun with friends\" width=\"380\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/lake-fun-with-friends.jpg 380w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/lake-fun-with-friends-228x300.jpg 228w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 380px) 100vw, 380px\" \/><\/center>It was so much fun and gave me that sense of seeing the world even though it was only for a day and less than 100 miles away.<\/p>\n<p>But as time went by I definitely wanted to go on more longer term, faraway trips.<\/p>\n<p>Here\u2019s how I handled that.<\/p>\n<p><strong>I\u2019d always heard about people collecting hundreds of thousands of points from credit cards and using them to fly for free, but I never understood how they did it.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>I thought they were wrecking their credit score or going into debt and just wrote it off as something that wouldn\u2019t work for me.<\/p>\n<p>Until this new phase of my life.<\/p>\n<p>I did some Googling and ended up finding a way to safely travel hack.<\/p>\n<p>I made <a href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/thehiddengreen\/videos\/535300473307213\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">this video<\/a> to show you how:<\/p>\n<p><center><iframe loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/plugins\/video.php?href=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2F%5Cthehiddengreen%2Fvideos%2F535300473307213%2F&amp;width=500&amp;show_text=false&amp;appId=1827641344215487&amp;height=280&amp;mute=0\" width=\"600\" height=\"320\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" data-mce-fragment=\"1\"><\/iframe><\/center>I\u2019d do this for 2-3 cards a year, which would give me enough miles for 2 or so free flights to places like Costa Rica to surf, or Colorado and Utah to snowboard.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55285\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/ryland-surfing.jpg\" alt=\"ryland surfing\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/ryland-surfing.jpg 500w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/ryland-surfing-300x200.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/center>All in all these little life-hacks probably helped me save an extra $10,000 a year. So over my near four years of work that was about an extra $40,000.<\/p>\n<p>Not bad!<\/p>\n<p>Once I saw how much money I was adding to my wallet with these type of acts, I started pushing my limits with it.<\/p>\n<p>And consistent with \u201cRyland\u201d fashion I pushed it a bit too far.<\/p>\n<h2>Girlfriend Ain\u2019t Having It<\/h2>\n<p>What do I mean by too far?<\/p>\n<p>Well, I got so into this \u201cspend as little as possible\u201d mindset that one day I became too paralyzed to even buy my girlfriend a birthday present.<\/p>\n<p>To say the least, my girlfriend wasn\u2019t having it (and rightly so).<\/p>\n<p>At this point, I had become overly focused on the \u201ccontrol my spending\u201d side of the game.<\/p>\n<p>I learned in that moment that the issue with only focusing on controlling my spending is it\u2019s limited \u2014 I could only budget so far until I felt scarcity.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-55286\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/enough-money-chart.jpg\" alt=\"enough money chart\" width=\"570\" height=\"298\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/enough-money-chart.jpg 622w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/enough-money-chart-300x157.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px\" \/><\/center>And scarcity isn\u2019t happiness.<\/p>\n<p>I was after freedom, not constriction.<\/p>\n<p>So if I was to continue on my path, I had to turn my focus to the other side of the game \u2014 <em>increasing my income.<\/em><\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-55287\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/net-worth-growth-chart.jpg\" alt=\"net worth growth chart\" width=\"584\" height=\"314\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/net-worth-growth-chart.jpg 640w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/net-worth-growth-chart-300x161.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 584px) 100vw, 584px\" \/><\/center>The beauty here is that the income side is unlimited. And if you play it right, you can align the income to come in by doing something you love.<\/p>\n<p>That\u2019s the ultimate goal \u2014 making enough money doing something you love.<\/p>\n<p>So off I went.<\/p>\n<h2>How I Handled My First Job (It Wasn\u2019t Pretty)<\/h2>\n<p>I\u2019ll never forget my first interview.<\/p>\n<p>It was in this tiny, awkwardly quiet white-walled meeting room.<\/p>\n<p>One of my future colleagues came in and it seemed like we had a good conversation. As we were wrapping things up he asked, \u201cAre you willing to shovel shit?\u201d<\/p>\n<p>It was kind of a test to make sure I had grit.<\/p>\n<p>Like any good interviewer, I said, \u201cGive me the shovel.\u201d<\/p>\n<p><strong>Horrible answer.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>I got the shovel and my first job title became &#8220;Chargeback Support Representative&#8221; making $47,000\/yr.<\/p>\n<p>You know when you see a charge for $132 that a fraudster stole from you and you call your bank?<\/p>\n<p>I was the person who picked up the phone.<\/p>\n<p>The thing was, I loved the company I worked for and I really believed in its mission, but I couldn\u2019t stand my position or my boss, and my work suffered because of it.<\/p>\n<p><strong>I wasn\u2019t a team player, I did C grade work on my daily tasks and I just wasn\u2019t myself.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>For two years I felt as if I would show up, do a couple tasks and accept the normal small raises for being a warm body in a chair.<\/p>\n<p>Then, right around that \u201cbirthday gift\u201d incident, I finally switched positions to one I knew I\u2019d enjoy more.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55288\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/partying-on-lawn.jpg\" alt=\"partying on lawn\" width=\"500\" height=\"369\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/partying-on-lawn.jpg 500w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/partying-on-lawn-300x221.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/center>Immediately I started adding value.<\/p>\n<p>I was excited to come into work, happy to go above and beyond and loved supporting my other teammates.<\/p>\n<p>This newfound energy led me to two raises in 10 months from $55k to $70k with bonuses.<\/p>\n<p><strong>If I could summarize the top things I did to get those raises it\u2019d be:<\/strong><\/p>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li>Asking my boss what the #1 thing I could do to be successful in my position. (Then doing it)<\/li>\n<li>Asking my boss what\u2019s the biggest thing she and the team needed help with outside my roles and responsibilities? (Then doing that also)<\/li>\n<li>And being kind, uplifting and helpful to everyone.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>Seriously. That\u2019s it.<\/p>\n<p>And when I decided it was time to transition away to work I enjoyed even more, I got notes like this:<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-55289\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/thank-you-work-email-note.jpg\" alt=\"thank you work email note\" width=\"600\" height=\"342\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/thank-you-work-email-note.jpg 640w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/thank-you-work-email-note-300x171.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/center>That note is worth a starting salary of $70k\/yr for me.<\/p>\n<p><strong>In other words, when I started adding value to the team I wasn\u2019t just getting paid more, I was also building my personal capital.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Think of it like this.<\/p>\n<p>Say I go to work each month to work on a house. Every two weeks rent comes in.<\/p>\n<p>If I put in new carpets, upgrade the utilities and paint the rooms while at work I could charge more for rent (increase my income) and know that the value of my house was going up (my personal capital).<\/p>\n<p>Everything was better with this new job.<\/p>\n<p>But within a year, I was ready to move on again toward my financially independent life.<\/p>\n<h2>Living a Financially Independent Life (Before Financial Independence)<\/h2>\n<p>A financially independent life.<\/p>\n<p>WTF is that anyway?<\/p>\n<p>Three years ago I would have told you I\u2019d be financially independent the moment my passive income covered my lifestyle cost.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55290\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/financial-freedom-emojis.jpg\" alt=\"financial freedom emojis\" width=\"191\" height=\"340\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/financial-freedom-emojis.jpg 191w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/financial-freedom-emojis-169x300.jpg 169w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 191px) 100vw, 191px\" \/><\/center>The problem with that definition though is it has nothing to do with life. It only touches on money.<\/p>\n<p>Today I believe it\u2019s totally different.<\/p>\n<p>Today I believe I can have a <em><strong>financially independent life<\/strong><\/em> as soon as I have enough money to have the confidence to walk away from any situation that doesn\u2019t benefit me.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55291\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/financially-independent-emojis.jpg\" alt=\"financially independent emojis\" width=\"271\" height=\"332\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/financially-independent-emojis.jpg 271w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/financially-independent-emojis-245x300.jpg 245w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 271px) 100vw, 271px\" \/><\/center><strong>That moment comes at different times for different people.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>For me, that moment hit about three years after my first journal entry when my girlfriend asked me this question, \u201cWhy not now?\u201d<\/p>\n<p>\u201cWhy not take off on your millennial adventure? Why not quit and start your own thing? You have the money.\u201d She said.<\/p>\n<p>She stumped me.<\/p>\n<p>(That girl\u2019s probably been my best financial advisor, haha)<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55292\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/yoga-posing-sunset.jpg\" alt=\"yoga posing sunset\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/yoga-posing-sunset.jpg 500w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/yoga-posing-sunset-300x225.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/center>I seriously didn\u2019t have a good answer.<\/p>\n<p>I had saved almost $100,000 (not including investment growth) and had a net worth that could cover 7 to 8 years of my lifestyle cost.<\/p>\n<p>She was right \u2014 why not now?<\/p>\n<p><strong>I took it to heart.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>I started writing my own blog about financial independence. I started helping my friends with their money situations just because I loved doing it. And I put up a page on my site about coaching other people in similar situations toward financial independence.<\/p>\n<p>One day a friend I had helped posted about working with me on his Facebook page.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-55293\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/hidden-green-recommendation.jpg\" alt=\"hidden green recommendation\" width=\"452\" height=\"448\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/hidden-green-recommendation.jpg 500w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/hidden-green-recommendation-125x125.jpg 125w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/hidden-green-recommendation-300x298.jpg 300w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/hidden-green-recommendation-144x144.jpg 144w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 452px) 100vw, 452px\" \/><\/center>As life goes, one of his friends saw it, came across the coaching page on my site and became my first client.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-55294\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/client-marketing-emojis.jpg\" alt=\"client marketing emojis\" width=\"601\" height=\"129\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/client-marketing-emojis.jpg 634w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/client-marketing-emojis-300x64.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 601px) 100vw, 601px\" \/><\/center>I then offered my small list of 200 readers early access to a course I was building on financial independence.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55295\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/free-early-member-access.jpg\" alt=\"free early member access\" width=\"500\" height=\"393\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/free-early-member-access.jpg 500w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/free-early-member-access-300x236.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/center>In that course, I didn\u2019t just sit back and send them the lessons. I engaged with them via email and live office hours on Facebook.<\/p>\n<p>From that group, my next two clients signed up.<\/p>\n<p>I gave my heart and soul to ensure every person I talked to kicked ass. Then when they became clients I continued with that kind of help which brought in new subscribers and new clients.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55296\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/insanely-helpul-marketing.jpg\" alt=\"insanely helpul marketing\" width=\"552\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/insanely-helpul-marketing.jpg 552w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/insanely-helpul-marketing-300x272.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 552px) 100vw, 552px\" \/><\/center>I\u2019ve had almost 20 clients since then.<\/p>\n<p>While all this was happening I took my girlfriend\u2019s advice, amicably left my job and gave a full shot at aligning my income to what I love even further.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Today I\u2019m still giving it that shot.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>It can be tough at times, but I know as long as I continue helping people as best I can the income side will follow.<\/p>\n<p>And beyond money, I\u2019m now working on the things I\u2019m passionate about. Like taking a few trips a year without breaking the bank. And I\u2019m on my way to making enough money doing something I love to live a fun, yet simple life.<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55297\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/ryland-mountains.jpg\" alt=\"ryland mountains\" width=\"429\" height=\"530\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/ryland-mountains.jpg 429w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/ryland-mountains-243x300.jpg 243w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 429px) 100vw, 429px\" \/><\/center>I got to this place not because of some rigid system.<\/p>\n<p><strong>I got here only because I kept <em>going<\/em>.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>That\u2019s it. That\u2019s the secret \u2014 keep going.<\/p>\n<p>I started this whole journey with tears rolling down my cheeks trying to build a budget that ended up looking like this:<\/p>\n<p><center><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-55257\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/youre-fcked-budget.jpg\" alt=\"youre f*cked budget\" width=\"500\" height=\"404\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/youre-fcked-budget.jpg 500w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/youre-fcked-budget-300x242.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/center>I didn\u2019t know how to make a budget (pretty obvious). I didn\u2019t know where to put my money. I didn\u2019t even know the difference between a savings and <a href=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/hm-bradley-a-3-interest-checking-account-based-on-your-savings-rate\/\">checking account<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>I just started writing.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Goals. Reflect.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>You can do that.<\/p>\n<p>You can start right now.<\/p>\n<p>It might make you a bit uncomfortable. Great! Embrace it.<\/p>\n<p><em><strong>Tell me the 4-6 things you want to accomplish deep down this month in the comments below.<\/strong><\/em><\/p>\n<p>Don\u2019t think. Just write.<\/p>\n<p>I\u2019ll hang out here for the day, reading your comments and doing my best to help you out.<\/p>\n<p>Thanks for reading,<\/p>\n<p>&#8211; Ryland<\/p>\n<p>**********<br \/>\n<em><strong>Ryland<\/strong> is a writer, outdoorsman and surfer. He\u2019s also the founder of The Hidden Green, which helps young professionals (the ones who\u2019d choose a mountain bike over a Maserati) do well with their finances. You&#8217;re invited to take <strong>The Hidden Green\u2019s FREE mini-course<\/strong> \u2014 Do What You Love Finance or reach out to Ryland at ryland@thehiddengreen.com.<\/em><\/p>\n<p><strong>[UPDATE:<\/strong> Blog and course\/email no longer active :( ]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>[Oh do I have a good story for you guys today!! I h